{
  "page": "Celia Tully",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Tully\" title=\"House Tully\"><img alt=\"House Tully.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/61/House_Tully.svg/50px-House_Tully.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/61/House_Tully.svg/75px-House_Tully.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/61/House_Tully.svg/100px-House_Tully.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">Celia Tully</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Tully\" title=\"House Tully\"><img alt=\"House Tully.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/61/House_Tully.svg/50px-House_Tully.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/61/House_Tully.svg/75px-House_Tully.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/61/House_Tully.svg/100px-House_Tully.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Tully\" title=\"House Tully\">House Tully</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Rivermen\" title=\"Rivermen\">Rivermen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Father</th><td>\nLord <a href=\"/index.php/House_Tully\" title=\"House Tully\">Tully</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Celia Tully</b> was a noblewoman from <a href=\"/index.php/House_Tully\" title=\"House Tully\">House Tully</a> during the reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_V_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon V Targaryen\">Aegon V Targaryen</a>. She was a daughter of the ruling <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Riverrun\" title=\"Lord of Riverrun\">Lord of Riverrun</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf_the_targaryen_kings:_aegon_v.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf_the_targaryen_kings:_aegon_v.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Celia_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Celia-2\">&#91;N 1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Celia_Tully&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_V_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon V Targaryen\">Aegon V Targaryen</a> and his wife, Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Betha_Blackwood\" title=\"Betha Blackwood\">Betha Blackwood</a>, made several <a href=\"/index.php/Betrothal\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Betrothal\">betrothals</a> for their children in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_237_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">237&#160;AC</a>, amongst them was Celia and Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys II Targaryen\">Jaehaerys</a>. However, the betrothal was broken by Jaehaerys three years later, and he married his sister, Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Shaera_Targaryen\" title=\"Shaera Targaryen\">Shaera</a>, for love instead.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf_the_targaryen_kings:_aegon_v.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf_the_targaryen_kings:_aegon_v.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Celia_Tully&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Celia-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Celia_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Given the succession of House Tully during the third century after Aegon's Conquest (<a href=\"/index.php/Medgar_Tully\" title=\"Medgar Tully\">Medgar</a>, his <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Tully_(successor_of_Medgar)\" title=\"Lord Tully (successor of Medgar)\">successor</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Tully_(father_of_Hoster)\" title=\"Lord Tully (father of Hoster)\">father of Hoster</a>, and then <a href=\"/index.php/Hoster_Tully\" title=\"Hoster Tully\">Hoster Tully</a>), this Lord Tully can only be either Medgar's successor or Hoster's father.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Celia_Tully&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf_the_targaryen_kings:_aegon_v.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf_the_targaryen_kings:_aegon_v.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf_the_targaryen_kings:_aegon_v.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Targaryen Kings: Aegon V.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403124543\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.087 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.310 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 541/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 10599/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 5365/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 569/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 1573/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.200/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 6.48 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  297.538      1 -total\n 94.56%  281.355      1 Template:Infobox_character\n 93.88%  279.327      1 Template:Infobox\n 13.15%   39.129     12 Template:Infobox_value\n  5.12%   15.232      4 Template:Infobox_label\n  2.25%    6.699      2 Template:Ref\n  1.39%    4.124      1 Template:Date\n  1.30%    3.860      2 Template:Ref/core\n  1.28%    3.794      2 Template:References\n  0.99%    2.959      1 Template:Notes\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:19121-0!canonical and timestamp 20260403124543 and revision id 295518\n -->\n",
